[Glastonbury is the site of the Glastonbury Festival of Contemporary Performing Arts, a performing arts festival, held in July, that takes place near Pilton, Somerset, England, best known for its contemporary music, but also for dance, comedy, theatre, circus, cabaret and other arts. Glastonbury is the largest greenfield festival in the world, and is now attended by at least 175 000 people, requiring extensive infrastructure in terms of security, transport, water and electricity supply. The majority of staff are volunteers, helping the festival to raise millions of pounds for good causes. There is consequently a large increase in the population of the area before, during and after the festival -- conditions favouring the spread of measles virus infection among young adults -- the segment of the population with the highest number of susceptible. A map of Somerset, showing the location of Glastonbury, can be accessed at http://www.bbc.co.uk/somerset/in_pictures/360_panoramas/index.shtml. - Mod.CP

